Comment: 0,0:02:22.54,0:02:23.46,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Ugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.21,0:02:25.17,Default,MT,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.83,0:02:27.92,Default,MT,0,0,0,,No!
Comment: 0,0:02:36.22,0:02:39.14,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Ooh. Oh.
Comment: 0,0:02:45.02,0:02:46.19,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.61,0:02:53.90,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Hey, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.90,0:02:54.99,Default,MT,0,0,0,,You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.46,0:03:11.50,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,That’s right.\NBack to the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.50,0:03:14.88,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Back to the train, \Nlike a good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.89,0:03:20.60,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,{\i1}I saw a train go racin’ by
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.60,0:03:23.22,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,{\i1}On exit day, on exit day
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.22,0:03:25.89,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,{\i1}I saw a train go racin’ by
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.89,0:03:28.56,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,{\i1}It gave a boy an exit
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.56,0:03:30.98,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,{\i1}What got left on the train that day
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.98,0:03:33.69,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,{\i1}On exit day, on exit day
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.69,0:03:37.36,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,{\i1}A lonely little sliver girl
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.36,0:03:42.24,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,{\i1}On exit day in the morning
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.49,0:03:44.16,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Or afternoon, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.16,0:03:47.08,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Not a lot of clocks\Non the train, are there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.79,0:03:49.71,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Ugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.71,0:03:51.21,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Shut it, skinsuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.21,0:03:52.04,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.13,0:03:55.63,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,what’s the plan now \Nyour boyfriend’s gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.63,0:03:57.22,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,little sliver girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.79,0:04:27.79,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,I didn’t see m’self goin’ out this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.79,0:04:29.96,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,How ’bout you, little sliver?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.96,0:04:33.80,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Was this the way you saw\Nyour glorious escape going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.38,0:04:37.30,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Eh, no matter.\NMy job is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.30,0:04:39.55,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,You’re as good\Nas sanded out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.80,0:04:41.22,Default,MT,0,0,0,,I’ll see about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.22,0:04:43.89,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,This was never gonna end well for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.89,0:04:45.72,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,You should’ve followed mirror law,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.72,0:04:47.23,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,and been recycled.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.23,0:04:50.35,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Or choose to become\Na disgusting flec like you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.35,0:04:51.15,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.15,0:04:52.31,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,What did you just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.31,0:04:53.36,Default,MT,0,0,0,,You’re a coward!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.36,0:04:55.69,Default,MT,0,0,0,,When your prime died,\Nyou chose to be a flec
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.69,0:04:57.90,Default,MT,0,0,0,,because you were afraid\Nto let go of your identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.90,0:05:01.36,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,It wasn’t about keeping\Nmy memories or identity!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.36,0:05:05.41,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,It was about respecting\Nthe balance our kind provides.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.41,0:05:06.54,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Ugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.54,0:05:08.08,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Why are you like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.08,0:05:10.41,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Was your last prime\Nthis much of a jerk,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.41,0:05:12.04,Default,MT,0,0,0,,or is this pure you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.24,0:05:48.79,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Why can’t I go forward?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.12,0:05:50.00,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,It’s...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.12,0:05:53.42,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,It’s— It’s the train!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.67,0:05:56.59,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.55,0:06:05.30,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Ahh!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.11,0:06:16.86,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Ahh!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.23,0:06:21.15,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.62,0:06:34.92,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Sliver girl, human boy,\Nand super deer!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.92,0:06:38.54,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Goin’ from car to car,\Nlearning lessons.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.54,0:06:40.34,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,What an adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.34,0:06:44.09,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,You really fancied yourself \Na regular passenger out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.09,0:06:44.84,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,didn’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.84,0:06:46.55,Default,MT,0,0,0,,I’ve been exploring the train,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.55,0:06:48.01,Default,MT,0,0,0,,same as Tulip or Jesse.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.01,0:06:49.26,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Oh, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.26,0:06:53.52,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,I mean, that must be why the train \Nis so keen on gettin’ you back,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.52,0:06:57.23,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,so it can help you get\Nyour shiny green number down,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.23,0:06:58.44,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,or— Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.44,0:07:00.32,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,So sorry. Forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.32,0:07:01.61,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,You don’t have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.61,0:07:03.11,Default,MT,0,0,0,,You don’t know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.11,0:07:04.36,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,What did you think would happen
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.36,0:07:06.53,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,if you were allowed \Nthrough the exit?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.53,0:07:08.95,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,You’d just go out\Ninto the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.95,0:07:11.49,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,with your metal skin\Nand your magic deer,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.49,0:07:12.41,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,and what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.41,0:07:13.45,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,High school?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.45,0:07:14.29,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Prom?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.29,0:07:15.50,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,College? Job?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.50,0:07:18.83,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,You and your prime,\Nwith parallel lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.83,0:07:20.04,Default,MT,0,0,0,,I would...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.04,0:07:21.75,Default,MT,0,0,0,,I-I’ll figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.42,0:07:27.01,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Th— The train \Nisn’t gonna let you exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.01,0:07:28.30,Default,MT,0,0,0,,The train can’t\Nstop me from—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.30,0:07:31.26,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Did you ever wonder\Nwhy that car was there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.26,0:07:32.97,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,The Mirrored Car,\Nthe Chrome Car,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.97,0:07:34.52,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,whatever you want to call it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.89,0:07:38.35,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Your prime couldn’t have\Ngotten out of the car
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.35,0:07:40.65,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,unless you switched.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.65,0:07:42.98,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,No one’s prime could have,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.98,0:07:47.82,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,so did the train make the car\Nso you could get out?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.82,0:07:50.41,Default,MT,0,0,0,,You’re... trying to freak me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.41,0:07:51.24,Default,MT,0,0,0,,It won’t work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.24,0:07:53.62,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Maybe the car was {\i1}for{\i0} you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.62,0:07:54.33,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Why would—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.33,0:07:57.50,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,To use you to help Tulip learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.50,0:08:01.29,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Just another creation \Nof the train, to help passengers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.29,0:08:02.34,Default,MT,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.34,0:08:03.67,Default,MT,0,0,0,,I’m a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.67,0:08:05.51,Default,MT,0,0,0,,I-I was making my own choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.51,0:08:07.22,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Oh, choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.22,0:08:10.39,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,And choices lead to lessons!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.39,0:08:13.31,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,And what were you\Nlearning, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.31,0:08:16.35,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,How to become what the boy\Nneeded you to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.35,0:08:17.81,Default,MT,0,0,0,,It wasn’t like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.81,0:08:20.10,Default,MT,0,0,0,,We were friends.\NWe {\i1}are{\i0} friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.10,0:08:23.40,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,But they all make friends,\Nthough, don’t they?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.40,0:08:25.44,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Companions?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.94,0:08:28.24,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Stop it!\NStop laughing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.24,0:08:31.95,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,You might even say \Nyou became his counterpart,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.95,0:08:34.70,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,might say you \Nbecame kind of a...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.54,0:08:36.37,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,reflection.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.37,0:08:37.46,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Ugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.46,0:08:38.21,Default,MT,0,0,0,,I hate you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.29,0:08:41.08,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,I-I don’t care.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.96,0:08:43.84,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,What, did you think you’re free?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.84,0:08:45.96,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,That— That you escaped?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.96,0:08:48.47,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,You’re just stuck on the train now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.47,0:08:50.76,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,You’re just in another mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.76,0:08:51.84,Default,MT,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.84,0:08:52.97,Default,MT,0,0,0,,It’s not like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.60,0:08:55.72,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Face it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.72,0:08:58.89,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Being a reflection\Nis all there is for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.89,0:09:01.85,Default,MT,0,0,0,,I don’t care what the train’s\Nbeen doing or why.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.85,0:09:05.02,Default,MT,0,0,0,,I know who I am, and Jesse\Ndidn’t want to leave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.02,0:09:07.36,Default,MT,0,0,0,,We’re friends,\Nand that’s real,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.36,0:09:09.15,Default,MT,0,0,0,,and I’ll get off the train\Nand find him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.15,0:09:10.36,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,Oh yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.36,0:09:11.91,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,You and what number?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.91,0:09:13.32,Default,MT,0,0,0,,I’ll get a number.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.32,0:09:14.16,Default,MT,0,0,0,,I’ll...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.12,0:09:16.62,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Those pods.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.62,0:09:19.08,Default,MT,0,0,0,,The ones that drop off\Nnew passengers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.08,0:09:20.54,Default,MT,0,0,0,,I’ll find one,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.54,0:09:22.25,Default,MT,0,0,0,,ride it back\Nto wherever it came from,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.25,0:09:24.75,Default,MT,0,0,0,,and I’ll make this train\Ngive me a number.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.67,0:09:27.25,Default,MT,0,0,0,,We’re going, Alan Dracula.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.77,0:09:46.98,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Alan Dracula, come on!
Comment: 0,0:10:06.29,0:10:07.13,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Ahhh!
Comment: 0,0:10:08.34,0:10:09.09,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Ah!
Comment: 0,0:10:09.09,0:10:09.92,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Wah!
Comment: 0,0:10:11.22,0:10:11.76,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.38,0:10:14.43,Default,MT,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.43,0:10:16.18,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,I’m as good as dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.18,0:10:19.89,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,and if my last act\Nis to bring you with me, sliver,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.89,0:10:23.14,Default,Mace,0,0,0,,I can’t imagine\Na better way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.14,0:10:24.77,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Well, I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.05,0:11:01.14,Default,MT,0,0,0,,Now, we wait for a pod.

